block_factorization.statement:
Let C ≠ C' be m-subsets of D with Phi_w(C)=Phi_w(C'). Set R = C ∩ C', U = C \\ C', V = C' \\ C, and s = |U| = |V|. Then:
  (i)   s ≥ w+1 and |R| = m−s ≤ m−w−1;
  (ii)  Λ_C = Λ_R Λ_U, Λ_{C'} = Λ_R Λ_V, and Λ_C − Λ_{C'} = Λ_R (Λ_U − Λ_V);
  (iii) deg(Λ_U − Λ_V) ≤ s − w − 1, hence Phi_w(U)=Phi_w(V);
  (iv)  |C △ C'| = 2s.

scale_dictionary.statement:
Under block factorization, s = |C \\ C'| satisfies:
  s = w+1  ⇔  |C △ C'| = 2(w+1)  ⇔  tight / min-weight (free-1 CS of (w+1)-blocks on core R);
  s ≥ w+2  ⇔  |C △ C'| ≥ 2(w+2)  ⇔  long trade / non-tight, and (U,V) is a multi-mate pair at parameters (s,w) with free_s = s−w ≥ 2.
